President Obama issued a statement recognizing the 37th anniversary of the Supreme Court decision in Roe v. Wade. He affirmed his support for every woman's constitutional right to choose whether to have an abortion, as well as the right to privacy from government intrusion. He also expressed his commitment to preventing unintended pregnancies, supporting pregnant women and families, and strengthening the adoption system. The President emphasized the importance of ensuring that all women have limitless opportunities to fulfill their dreams.